title: Cards, 1889
provenance: A present for the tenth wedding anniversary of Mr. and Mrs. George T. Bliss, February 12, 1889.
description:
Sheet metal. On one side, engraved script reading "Feb. 12, 1879-1889". Reverse, plain. Corners cut at angle of 45 degrees. Small punched hole with yellowed ribbon in upper left corner.

Formerly known as- n-a-703

tombstone.epitaph:
Cards, 1889.
1889. Metal. Gift of Anonymous Donor. 1937-45-5-b.
